title: Why can this closure use v without having received it as an argument?
pid: 8ea4034e-c106-450e-b3d4-f1c3d05327f6
body: |2-
  use std::thread;

  fn main() {
      let v = vec![1, 2, 3];

      let handle = thread::spawn(move || {
          println!("Here's a vector: {v:?}");
      });

      handle.join().unwrap();
  }
